                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18171203-24-off141 t18171203-24-crimeloc144"></join>. On the 5th of November, about twelve o'clock, the prisoner came in, and asked the price of a handkerchief; he said it would not do, and went out; I missed the shoes, and ran out and took him with them in his possession - He begged for mercy; there was another person in the shop.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was going to show them to a man.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 23.</p>
